*---------------------*
| Compute noised mesh |
*---------------------*

With choice of type of noise :
- gaussian on each coordinate : "Cubic" ;
- idem in a sphere : "Spheric" ;
- gaussian along the normal of each point  : "Normal".
You can choose also the magnitude of noise ( in % of the longest diagonal of the bounding box )

Input : A mesh ( OFF file )
-------

Output : The noised mesh
--------

To compile  :
-------------

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
cmake .. # two times to include -std=gnu++0x for the random generator, weird... 
make

To use :
--------



./createNoise path/to/the/mesh.off option magnitude

where option is :
-c for "Cubic" noise
-s for "Spheric" noise
-n for "Normal" noise

example :
./createNoise ../knot.off -c 0.02

